Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.54,0:00:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Nationwide Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} Competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:05.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From all of the people with the Kojima surname in Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.11,0:00:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The best was to be determined - that's\Nwhat the Nichiuri TV special was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.64,0:00:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The winner's prize was ten million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.10,0:00:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, they also would receive a scroll as a bonus prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.32,0:00:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Painted by the ink-and-wash prodigy...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.28,0:00:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one of the boar-deer-butterfly trio - the "bush clover and boar."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.24,0:00:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta's dad was also participating in the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.75,0:00:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The preliminary rounds consisted of a push-up and\Na singing test, as well as a kanji writing quiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.96,0:00:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The evaluation was quite a tough one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.38,0:00:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were only three participants who passes\Nthe harsh tests and went to the final round.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.47,0:00:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surprisingly, Genta's dad was among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.95,0:00:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, just as the final round was about to start...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.77,0:00:55.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The president of the Kojima Group who\Nhosted this competition, Kojima Gonsaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.60,0:00:55.79,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\3c&H4B0D23&}Kojima Gonsaku (71)\N{\fs13}Kojima Group President
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.52,0:00:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was killed by someone who pushed him down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.40,0:01:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only people who used the stairs were the three finalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.24,0:01:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Genta's dad has become one of the suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.66,0:01:14.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, which of them is Genta's dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.81,0:01:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is magic, attack the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On Saturday nights, be sure to click on Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.37,0:01:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mystery of the case and the identity of Genta's dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.41,0:01:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will both be revealed at last!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.27,0:01:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.89,0:01:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.76,0:01:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.75,0:03:21.01,title001,,0,0,0,,{\t(0,3260,\fs17\fad(0,50)}Waiting Room A
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.37,0:03:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,waiting room\NWhile I was waiting in this hikaeshitsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.96,0:03:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard a door being knocked on elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.88,0:03:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I heard a scream and a loud noise so I went out to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.14,0:03:35.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's when I was that old man lying\Nat the bottom of the stairs, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.27,0:03:34.47,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\fad(250,250)}Kojima Bunta (33)\N{\fs13}Participant
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.85,0:03:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you leave the room immediately after the scream and noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.48,0:03:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I waited for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.82,0:03:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was just another kind of test.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.44,0:03:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, was happyakuichi - 801 really what was written on the paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.82,0:03:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.49,0:03:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, how many push-ups did you complete in three minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.38,0:04:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.88,0:04:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.80,0:04:09.81,title002,,0,0,0,,Waiting Room B
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.26,0:04:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You also heard someone knocking on the door of another room...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.22,0:04:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after hearing the scream and loud noise...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.72,0:04:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You rushed out of the room and hurried to the scene, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.10,0:04:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.10,0:04:25.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After I heard the ruckus and opened my door...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.76,0:04:28.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I saw the other two were coming out too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.28,0:04:27.91,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\fad(250,250)}Kojima Genji (32)\N{\fs13}Participant
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.53,0:04:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, on that piece of paper was something you claimed was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.66,0:04:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One foot, eight inches\NYes, shakuhachi - bamboo flute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.78,0:04:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,801 and 1'8"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.25,0:04:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only the "8" matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.75,0:04:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what song did you sing today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.29,0:04:45.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kuroda Bushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.75,0:04:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want me to sing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.34,0:04:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.05,0:04:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you would, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:54.81,title002,,0,0,0,,Waiting Room C
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.30,0:04:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah; it's the same as those other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.55,0:04:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard a loud scream and noise so I rushed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.10,0:05:03.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's when I saw the old man lying all\Nby himself on the floor downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:03.78,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\fad(250,250)}Kojima Gankichi (34)\N{\fs13}Participant
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, was the word ippin - first-class - really written on that paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.45,0:05:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ippin" as in "the world's first-class item."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.74,0:05:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, can you write the kanji for "rose"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.45,0:05:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rose...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.08,0:05:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't possibly write the kanji for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:27.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what was all of that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.54,0:05:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.30,0:05:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:33.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} asked you to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.37,0:05:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.82,0:05:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said if we asked them those questions, we might\Nfind out the real purpose for this competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.04,0:05:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi, how'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.08,0:05:48.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Push-ups... about a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.27,0:05:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Singing was about at Inspector Megure's level.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he couldn't write the kanji for "rose."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.68,0:05:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My singing is better that his, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also messed up the lyrics of Kuroda Bushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He messed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.62,0:06:03.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.00,0:06:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\1}[Drink and win this best spear in Japan]\N"Hi no moto ichi no kono yari wo."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.42,0:06:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he mistook it as...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.51,0:06:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shi no moto ichi no."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.06,0:06:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.64,0:06:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recorded the song as well as the investigative interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.60,0:06:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Want to hear them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.02,0:06:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what can we learn from that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.65,0:06:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This competition wasn't about being number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.32,0:06:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.28,0:06:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.70,0:06:46.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We all thought the contest was to choose the best Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.79,0:06:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we sent the push-up records to the\Nevaluation room where the president was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.88,0:06:54.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already finished the evaluation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.84,0:06:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's these 58 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:06:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is what he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.72,0:07:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before he saw the records?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.64,0:07:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the same situation for the kanji test.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.27,0:07:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just went to look at the video tape\Nrecording of the participants for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.19,0:07:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the singing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.90,0:07:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He listened to each of the contestants' recordings himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only the president was evaluating?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.20,0:07:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, seems like the president wanted to handle it all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.12,0:07:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the numbered shirts and shoes for the\Nparticipants were prepared by the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what standard did he use to evaluate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.63,0:07:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.26,0:07:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside the president's bag in the evaluation room...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.68,0:07:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was a gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.64,0:07:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.14,0:07:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with that, this paper too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.31,0:07:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.94,0:07:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's written with messy handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.40,0:07:55.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Regarding the scrolls - the first-class items of the world..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.86,0:07:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We have indeed obtained them."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:08:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"With respect - Hyakki Yakou."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.41,0:08:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hyakki Yakou...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.20,0:08:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderous robbery group?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.41,0:08:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.75,0:08:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president wrote in his blog that,\Namong the "boar-deer-butterfly"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.46,0:08:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had misplaced the deer and butterfly scrolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.96,0:08:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they were actually snatched by that gang six months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.47,0:08:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, the boar scroll was sent for repair, so it was not taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, was anyone killed at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.02,0:08:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.85,0:08:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president, his wife, and his servants\Nwere merely drugged and knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the president's pet dog Gonta...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its head was cut off by the group leader in the front yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.45,0:08:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And apparently, as the leader was\Nleaving, he was muttering something...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The barely conscious president overheard him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.50,0:08:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll spare your life since we have the same surname."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We might even be distant relatives."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.25,0:09:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you report that incident to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.51,0:09:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the president ordered me not to say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.43,0:09:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Detective Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.56,0:09:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, those three suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.77,0:09:19.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, all three were like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.57,0:09:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.82,0:09:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.82,0:09:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.20,0:09:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the president asked you to keep silent...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.66,0:09:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that robber group broke into your house and took the scrolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.83,0:09:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should have informed us police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.88,0:09:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.88,0:09:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, he said, "I will avenge Gonta's death, so don't tell anyone."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.09,0:09:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be this Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\NCompetition organized by the president was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.43,0:09:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.52,0:09:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't to choose the best Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.73,0:09:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was to find the one who killed Gonta and avenge its death...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.03,0:10:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the gun he had hidden in the evaluation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, for the surname Kojima, you could\Nwrite it as 小島 or 児島 or something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.58,0:10:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But all the participants here spelled Kojima as 小嶋.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.37,0:10:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.83,0:10:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.09,0:10:24.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three finalists spelled Kojima as 小 for "ko" and 嶋 for "jima."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.93,0:10:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, the president spelled his surname the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.93,0:10:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean the president knew the gang leader's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.81,0:10:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.85,0:10:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.27,0:10:40.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With those words left by the leader...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.19,0:10:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll spare your life since we have the same surname."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.90,0:10:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We might even be distant relatives."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.28,0:10:49.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.62,0:10:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only relatives would have the exact same surname and spelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:54.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.62,0:10:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could've chosen the participants with the same\Nsurnames during the application form screening process.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.63,0:11:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.09,0:11:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought it was strange when we saw all of\Nthe contestants wrote Kojima the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.22,0:11:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.68,0:11:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it makes sense up to here, how\Ndid he narrow it down from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.43,0:11:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, for the push-up test, the shoes worn by the\Nparticipants were prepared by the president, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.23,0:11:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.15,0:11:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you checked the shoe sizes of everyone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.45,0:11:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.45,0:11:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were told by the president to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.99,0:11:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, wasn't Gonta killed in the front yard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.79,0:11:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what is it you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.83,0:11:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was in the yard, don't they have to be at the scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.92,0:11:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.09,0:11:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, the shoe prints!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president pretended it was a physical test...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.34,0:11:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And narrowed down the participants by their shoe size!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the singing test was to hear their voices?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.81,0:11:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.77,0:12:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the president heard the leader's voice, there's no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.77,0:12:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the three finalists all have similar voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.28,0:12:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the kanji test was to see their handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.16,0:12:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To compare with this gang leader's handwriting on this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.41,0:12:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the leader wouldn't have used his\Nusual handwriting for the letter, would he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think either he attempted a different handwriting style...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.93,0:12:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or he asked someone else to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what's the purpose for the kanji test?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The handedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.60,0:12:44.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the dog was killed with a knife, he could tell from\Nthe wound which hand the leader used, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.86,0:12:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three had the same handedness, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.86,0:12:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.03,0:12:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Kojima Bunta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} lit up his cigarette...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.49,0:12:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Kojima Genji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drank from his cup...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.70,0:12:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Kojima Gankichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wiped his sweat with a towel...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.66,0:13:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three used their left hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.42,0:13:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.08,0:13:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he can narrow them down just by watching\Nthe VTR of the contestants doing the kanji quiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But aside from the voice, why not make them report their\Nshoe sizes and their handedness on their applications?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:21.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think if he did that, the culprit might realize\Nthis was about finding the dog's killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.19,0:13:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But boy, that's a great deduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I messaged a teenage detective I know, and this is what he told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.41,0:13:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it really was Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.20,0:13:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question now is, what was written on the paper\Nthe president asked the finalists to read?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that after making them read it, he knew\Nwho the culprit was and went to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which resulted in a fight for that paper, leading to his fall and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.84,0:13:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But all three answered differently after reading that piece of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, we searched their bodies and their waiting\Nrooms, but there was no sign of the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.40,0:14:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for where the paper is, Shinichi-niichan said he already knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.65,0:14:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, he also knows what was on the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.62,0:14:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is really late.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.75,0:14:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s dad really is involved in some kind of a case?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.63,0:14:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's just leave it to Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.26,0:14:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.46,0:14:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, don't make such a face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.43,0:14:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait for his return.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.93,0:14:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.97,0:14:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s dad would never do anything bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not really worried about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.77,0:14:49.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking it would be bad if a fight started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.77,0:14:51.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.15,0:14:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.40,0:14:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dad is combative, honest, and hates dishonorable things...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.99,0:15:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Combative...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.99,0:15:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honest...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hates dishonorable things...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.75,0:15:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a typical Tokyoite.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.92,0:15:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I have to go take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.13,0:15:14.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.34,0:15:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.31,0:15:21.77,title002,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,0)}Waiting Room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.18,0:15:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gathering us in such a room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.52,0:15:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you finish your interrogation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.10,0:15:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you know who the culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.77,0:15:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.48,0:15:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to confirm how you read the words on the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Happyakuichi - 801!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.66,0:15:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shakuhachi - bamboo flute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.28,0:15:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ippin - first class!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.41,0:15:46.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a number that was written!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.58,0:15:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what I said was a number too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:15:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut the shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.29,0:15:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious that it was kanji!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.96,0:15:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think those three saw different pieces of paper...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.14,0:16:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paper probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had this on it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.14,0:16:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.81,0:16:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, isn't that 801?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.02,0:16:13.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I saw it upside-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.15,0:16:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was 108.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.53,0:16:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So by "shakuhachi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.40,0:16:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You meant "hyakuhachi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.91,0:16:23.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,108 was what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.58,0:16:26.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What nonsense are you guys talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.66,0:16:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this "first class" as in "the world's first-class item"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.84,0:16:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sort of looks that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.84,0:16:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's hard to read it as the kanji for "item"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.84,0:16:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.14,0:16:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kanji "品" was written in circles\Ninstead of the proper tetragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.93,0:16:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you aren't used to this kind of\Nwriting, you wouldn't read this as "item."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.40,0:16:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.65,0:16:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The leader of the robber group.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.74,0:17:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, the word "item" as in "first-class\Nitems of the world" on the letter was also like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.58,0:17:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course they're the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.37,0:17:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I asked Detective Chiba to copy the words from the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.58,0:17:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.17,0:17:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president also copied the words to that\Nwashi paper and made you read them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.80,0:17:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And whoever read it as kanji instead\Nof numbers would be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.05,0:17:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, you were the one who fell for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hell're you saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.85,0:17:33.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to accuse me, then show me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.10,0:17:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That washi you're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.77,0:17:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, mister, do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.15,0:17:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That washi was specially made from mulberry of the fig family...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.32,0:17:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's extremely toxic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.45,0:17:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So even if you accidentally licked it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.75,0:17:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.21,0:17:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:17:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call an ambulance, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.71,0:18:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.88,0:18:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That washi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.38,0:18:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're confessing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.18,0:18:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were fighting over the paper with the president...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.80,0:18:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And made him fall down the stairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.43,0:18:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then left him alone and fled?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.73,0:18:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I confess...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.69,0:18:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I confess!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and call the ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.94,0:18:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you also confess to being the leader of the robber group?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.94,0:18:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.45,0:18:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the leader of Hyakki Yakou!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.91,0:18:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old man, as soon as he came into my room...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:31.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He grinned and said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long time no see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.04,0:18:36.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who killed my dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.15,0:18:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew you would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.80,0:18:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would want to get that boar scroll you failed to get last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.14,0:18:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, don't you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.47,0:18:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Depending on how you respond, I might even forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.14,0:18:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to run away, I won't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:18:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll just report it to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.86,0:19:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your face has already been captured by the TV cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.36,0:19:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, I have this piece of paper as evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.12,0:19:10.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I was doomed when he said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.87,0:19:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I tried to snatch away that evidential paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.95,0:19:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that old guy fell down the stairs just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.21,0:19:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you left the president alone and fled...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.00,0:19:22.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And swallowed that paper to destroy evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.26,0:19:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So go call an ambulance already!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.68,0:19:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.10,0:19:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's normal to use mulberry in making washi paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.02,0:19:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's not that toxic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.06,0:19:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.27,0:19:39.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But mulberries, unlike you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.81,0:19:41.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the skins are black, their insides are white.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.48,0:19:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a black-hearted man like you, isn't it a good medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll talk about this at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.95,0:19:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah, it was all a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was fooling around with what the brat said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.62,0:19:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.50,0:19:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.92,0:20:03.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Nuff with playin' innocent already!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.84,0:20:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatcha just said, I've heard everything clearly with mah ears!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't 'cha go tryin' to talk shit now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.64,0:20:14.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said I was joking...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.77,0:20:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still tryin' to play dumb, ya poor bastage!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.10,0:20:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-Bastage?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.85,0:20:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I own a bar, so what kinda drunkard haven't I seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.86,0:20:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll tell ya what!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.57,0:20:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't I reach my fingernails deep into ya throat...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And dig that washi up together with ya lunch!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.45,0:20:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.76,0:20:38.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.33,0:20:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.29,0:20:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.04,0:20:44.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.25,0:20:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.59,0:20:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s dad is the culprit!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.66,0:22:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.88,0:22:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.97,0:22:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.64,0:22:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with those glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.14,0:22:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, these...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.73,0:22:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom made you wear them?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.15,0:22:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because of the contest?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.73,0:22:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.94,0:22:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said they'd make me look smarter, and\Nkept naggin' me 'bout wearin' them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.61,0:22:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like they were your granny's glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.62,0:22:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're so strong that I could hardly open my eyes with 'em on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.20,0:22:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she kept naggin' me about "using\Nproper language" and "not to pick fights."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.71,0:22:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you answer with "bamboo flute"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.84,0:22:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, we heard about it from Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.47,0:22:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pronounced 108 as shakuhachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.22,0:23:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he's a Tokyoite.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.93,0:23:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For native Tokyoites, when they try to pronounce "hi" or "hya"...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.27,0:23:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It usually comes out as "shi" or "sha."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.90,0:23:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you could call it a dialect.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.49,0:23:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, when you sang the Kuroda Bushi song...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.65,0:23:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You turned "Hi no moto ichi no kono\Nyari wo," into "Shi no moto ichi", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.37,0:23:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how you hear it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.08,0:23:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.54,0:23:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how you knew he was Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.00,0:23:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.88,0:23:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,waiting room\NThe other two could pronounce "hikaeshitsu" and "himself" properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.63,0:23:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.84,0:23:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we had come any later, you'd have started fighting, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.10,0:23:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, don't be mindin' the details!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.97,0:23:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fires and fights are the flowers of Edo, they say!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.73,0:23:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a pretty ancient saying, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.70,0:23:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The prosecution's takeover will commence as planned, 4:00pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.66,0:24:00.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.70,0:24:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He faced the window and threw the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.54,0:24:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The prosecution's takeover is at 4:00pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.37,0:24:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the time limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.77,0:24:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.92,0:24:31.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Left-Handed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.06,0:24:32.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What's Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.23,0:24:33.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm a handy guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.43,0:24:34.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's not the right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.06,0:24:36.41,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode
